From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sound Tester <soundtester@invalid>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: audioinjector-octo: set the card owner

snd_soc_audioinjector_octo does not set .owner, so snd_soc_bind_card()
passes a NULL module to snd_card_new(), which trips WARN_ON(!module) at
sound/core/init.c:305. Every boot therefore prints a WARNING with a full
backtrace through audioinjector_octo_probe() and sets TAINT_WARN.

The card still registers and audio works, so the practical damage is not
to the audio path: it is that a measurement appliance ships with a
tainted kernel and a scary audio-stack backtrace in dmesg, which teaches
whoever reads the log to ignore exactly the place this card's real bug
(TDM slot rotation, "I2S SYNC error!") shows up.

Every other machine driver in sound/soc/bcm/ sets .owner. Do the same;
it also fixes the missing module refcount while the card is in use.

Signed-off-by: Sound Tester <soundtester@invalid>
---
 sound/soc/bcm/audioinjector-octo-soundcard.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/bcm/audioinjector-octo-soundcard.c b/sound/soc/bcm/audioinjector-octo-soundcard.c
--- a/sound/soc/bcm/audioinjector-octo-soundcard.c
+++ b/sound/soc/bcm/audioinjector-octo-soundcard.c
@@ -252,6 +252,7 @@

 static struct snd_soc_card snd_soc_audioinjector_octo = {
 	.name = "audioinjector-octo-soundcard",
+	.owner = THIS_MODULE,
 	.dai_link = audioinjector_octo_dai,
 	.num_links = ARRAY_SIZE(audioinjector_octo_dai),

